# MCP Server Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .vscode/mcp.env and set your tokens.
# NEVER commit .vscode/mcp.env — it is gitignored for security.
#
# To create a GitHub PAT:
#   1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens?type=beta
#   2. Create a Fine-grained token with these permissions:
#      - Repository access: loofi-fedora-tweaks
#      - Permissions: Contents (read), Issues (read/write), Pull requests (read/write),
#        Code security (read), Secret scanning (read)
#   3. Copy the token below
#
# If your token was ever committed to git, ROTATE IT IMMEDIATELY:
#   https://github.com/settings/tokens → Regenerate or delete the compromised token

GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN=ghp_replace_with_your_personal_access_token
